overview: The user initiated the conversation by expressing a desire to improve
  the aesthetics of their sleep questionnaire app, feeling it lacked visual
  appeal and personality. The agent took a systematic approach, first conducting
  a thorough review of the app's existing styling by examining global CSS,
  layout files, and various UI components and sections. This analysis revealed a
  generic color palette, plain backgrounds, and functional but uninspired form
  elements. Based on this, the agent developed a strategy to introduce a more
  sophisticated, calming, and sleep-themed design. The implementation involved
  updating the color palette to use deeper indigo/purple tones with teal
  accents, enhancing the main questionnaire form's layout and progress bar, and
  refining the styling of the intro and report sections. Key UI components like
  checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders were also updated to align with the new
  aesthetic, resulting in a more polished and inviting user experience.
